<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>This is extremely minor, but Zend_Console_Getopt throws a warning if you pass a null as the first argument of the constructor (indicating your command line script doesn't take any flags), and then call parse():</p>

<p>Code Sample:</p>

<p>$opts = new Zend_Console_Getopt(null);
$opts-&gt;parse();</p>

<p>If you call it without arguments (e.g. 'myscript.php') it works fine, but with an invalid argument (e.g. 'myscript.php -x') it will print a warning:</p>

<p>Warning: Invalid argument supplied for foreach() in Zend/Console/Getopt.php on line 609</p>

